05:19.640 --> 05:22.689
Grandma? Papa?

05:38.200 --> 05:40.965
Grandma? Papa?

05:42.440 --> 05:45.011
Honey, hold on. Hold on, hon.

05:46.440 --> 05:47.805
OK, come in.

05:57.800 --> 05:58.801
Hey.

05:59.000 --> 06:00.490
Where's Grandma?

06:00.640 --> 06:04.770
She's not here. Come give Papa a kiss.

06:10.640 --> 06:11.880
How's my PUPPY?

06:12.040 --> 06:13.371
Mm.

06:14.280 --> 06:16.726
Is Grandma gonna take me to school?

06:18.360 --> 06:21.125
I don't know. I think, um...

06:23.120 --> 06:25.964
I think I'm gonna take you to school.

06:28.320 --> 06:30.561
Can you finish getting ready?

06:30.720 --> 06:32.290
- Yes.
- OK.

07:00.520 --> 07:01.851
What's going on?

07:03.000 --> 07:05.241
You need to comb out my hair.

07:06.840 --> 07:11.050
- Really? You... You can't do that yet?
- Nope.

07:20.840 --> 07:24.606
Not from the top down,
from the bottom up.

07:26.240 --> 07:27.685
<i>GK.</i>

07:29.800 --> 07:31.086
Wow.

07:54.400 --> 07:58.166
- This is every day?
- Yup.

08:03.600 --> 08:07.241
- Eloise! We can't be late, honey.
- OK.

08:08.440 --> 08:10.841
Wait, wait, wait. Shut the door.

08:12.560 --> 08:16.724
- Here. Put this in my hair, please.
- Your hair?

08:17.480 --> 08:18.970
<i>GK.</i>

08:27.760 --> 08:30.445
Rosita, can you help me
find my sunglasses, please?

08:30.600 --> 08:32.328
- All right.
- There you go.

08:35.320 --> 08:38.289
You tied it like a tennis shoe.
It needs a bow.

08:38.440 --> 08:40.124
- Like Grammie does it.
- All right.

08:40.280 --> 08:41.486
Come redo it.

08:43.080 --> 08:44.570
Let me try again.

08:49.400 --> 08:51.050
All right, there's your bow.

08:55.120 --> 08:56.087
Now what?

08:56.240 --> 08:57.651
You're supposed to make me
brush my teeth.

08:57.800 --> 09:00.451
- I am?
- Yes. Grammie makes me every day.

09:00.640 --> 09:03.530
- Forces me.
- All right, well then, you...

09:04.480 --> 09:07.484
You get up there and you brush
your teeth, young lady. Right now.

09:07.640 --> 09:09.244
Say it like you mean it.

09:09.440 --> 09:12.887
Well, I mean it, all right?
I mean business. Right now!

09:13.880 --> 09:15.769
Good job.

09:20.960 --> 09:23.201
- Are you lost?
- No, I um...

09:23.360 --> 09:25.727
I thought it was on this street.
I'm just...

09:26.640 --> 09:29.769
I'm on the wrong street.

09:32.800 --> 09:35.326
Thought it was somewhere else.

09:35.480 --> 09:37.164
Isn't that called being lost?

09:37.320 --> 09:38.765
Yes, normally.

09:38.920 --> 09:43.642
I mean, it could be, but it isn't now,
right? I'm... not lost.

09:46.400 --> 09:48.641
How come you don't know?
You come to school every day.

09:48.800 --> 09:50.040
You don't know how to get here?

09:50.160 --> 09:52.208
I'm not driving.
I'm sitting in the back.

09:53.480 --> 09:56.484
If you're lost, you can tell me.
I don't care, Papa.

10:01.800 --> 10:03.564
Yes, I'm lost.

10:11.240 --> 10:13.322
We've gotta hurry up.
They're all inside already.

10:13.480 --> 10:16.484
I know, Puppy, I know.
OK, we're right here. See?

10:18.240 --> 10:20.208
I'm gonna be late!
They're all already in there.

10:20.360 --> 10:21.850
It's OK.
Just tell them your grandfather got...

10:22.000 --> 10:25.607
- Got lost?
- Yes, you can tell them I got lost.

10:25.760 --> 10:29.207
- Does that make you happy?
- It does.

10:31.400 --> 10:32.606
Go on.

10:49.200 --> 10:51.202
<i>I didn't have
the strength to tell her.</i>

10:51.360 --> 10:54.523
<i>Now I'm terrified that one of the kids
in her class will say something to her.</i>

10:54.680 --> 10:57.251
I need to be there
when she gets out of school.

10:57.400 --> 10:59.448
I need to tell her.

11:00.440 --> 11:02.727
It's OK. You'll tell her.

11:02.880 --> 11:05.929
Uh, meantime, we have some
good food here for you both to eat.

11:06.080 --> 11:10.847
Yeah, I was calling about
a memorial service and a burial.

11:11.000 --> 11:14.527
Um... I had spoken to Father Mackley.

11:14.680 --> 11:16.762
He suggested I give you a call.

11:19.440 --> 11:23.001
I'm gonna make some dishes for you,
Elliott, some pre-cooked things

11:23.200 --> 11:24.406
for you two to nibble on.

11:24.560 --> 11:27.245
OK.

11:30.720 --> 11:34.008
Uh, do you need to call her grandmother?
Reggie's mother?

11:34.160 --> 11:35.321
What does she call her, "Wee Wee"?

11:35.480 --> 11:36.970
- Grandma Wee Wee?
- Yeah.

11:37.120 --> 11:38.690
Why would I call her, Rick?

11:38.880 --> 11:40.882
I mean, really,
why would I call any of them?

11:41.040 --> 11:43.202
We're not related. All right?

11:43.360 --> 11:45.727
Carol wasn't related to them.

11:46.680 --> 11:51.322
Guess if I was gonna... call anybody,
it'd be that piece of shit son of hers

11:51.520 --> 11:54.444
that nobody's seen or heard from
in three years.

11:55.360 --> 11:58.921
Believe me, the last person I need
swarming around me right now

11:59.080 --> 12:01.082
is Grandma Wee Wee.

12:01.280 --> 12:04.602
Bad enough I have... you two.

12:07.160 --> 12:08.366
Sorry.

12:13.000 --> 12:15.810
You didn't have to do this, you know.
I could've...

12:16.000 --> 12:18.321
- I could've come on my own.
- Oh, come on.

12:18.480 --> 12:21.006
- We want to be with you right now.
- What a pretty school.

12:21.160 --> 12:24.323
I heard it's like one of the best ever.

12:26.840 --> 12:29.730
- Tell me your name again?
- Fay.

12:29.880 --> 12:31.450
That's right.

12:31.640 --> 12:33.483
You're right, Fay.

12:33.640 --> 12:34.687
Hey, there she is.

12:34.840 --> 12:36.524
Hey, are you sure you're up for this?

12:36.680 --> 12:38.808
Why don't I just grab her,
we'll take her back to the house,

12:38.960 --> 12:41.486
- tell her later when you're...
- I'm fine. Relax, Rick.

12:42.520 --> 12:45.922
Fay?

12:49.000 --> 12:51.321
That ain't gonna help.

12:56.720 --> 13:02.363
Papa, Andi Jacobson wants me to come
over and scrapbook at her house today.

13:02.520 --> 13:03.885
You want to do that?

13:04.040 --> 13:09.126
Go scrapbook over at
Andi Jack... ogym... Johnson's house?

13:09.280 --> 13:12.329
No. But I told her I'd ask you.

13:13.240 --> 13:15.766
Well, you did. You asked and I said no.

13:15.920 --> 13:17.081
Thank you.

13:18.560 --> 13:21.086
Let's go over here for a minute, Eloise.

13:22.840 --> 13:24.649
Talk with you about something.

13:31.320 --> 13:35.211
We had a bad night last night,
Eloise, you and I.

13:37.920 --> 13:41.083
Grandma Carol was killed in a accident.

13:41.920 --> 13:43.126
A car accident.

13:44.000 --> 13:45.809
A man hit her and...

13:48.840 --> 13:53.209
and she and he and several others,

13:53.360 --> 13:55.169
they're all gone.

13:56.200 --> 13:57.531
Have you been drinking?

13:58.520 --> 14:02.002
I... I have, yes. That's why, um...

14:02.920 --> 14:06.049
That's why Rick and his girlfriend Fudge
are out there in the car,

14:06.240 --> 14:08.846
'cause I've had a few drinks.

14:09.000 --> 14:12.322
I don't like it when you drink.

14:12.480 --> 14:13.766
I know.

14:14.920 --> 14:16.524
Her name isn't Fudge.

14:16.680 --> 14:19.729
- Rick's girlfriend, it isn't Fudge.
- Who said it was Fudge?

14:19.920 --> 14:21.809
- It couldn't be. You did.
- No.

14:22.000 --> 14:23.604
You said Rick and his girlfriend, Fudge.

14:23.800 --> 14:26.041
No, I said it was, um...

14:26.600 --> 14:27.761
it was...

14:32.760 --> 14:36.242
- I actually don't remember her name.
- Her name, it isn't Fudge.

14:36.400 --> 14:38.846
- I just know that.
- No, no. No, no, of course not.

14:39.000 --> 14:41.002
It couldn't be Fudge.

14:46.200 --> 14:50.649
I'm so sorry about your grandma, Eloise.

14:52.280 --> 14:54.647
I know you loved her a lot.

14:54.800 --> 14:59.044
And she loved you so very much.

15:00.920 --> 15:02.490
I'm sorry.

15:07.920 --> 15:12.403
- Are you OK, Pup?
- No. I'm super sad.

15:17.800 --> 15:19.643
So am I, sweetheart.

15:25.160 --> 15:27.845
It's the worst day of my life.

15:33.160 --> 15:36.801
<i>♪ Put a candle in the window</i>

15:39.360 --> 15:43.524
<i>♪ 'Cause I feel I've got to move</i>

15:44.680 --> 15:48.844
<i>♪ Though I'm gone, gone</i>

15:49.000 --> 15:52.288
<i>♪ I'll be coming home soon</i>

15:54.720 --> 15:58.805
<i>♪ Long as I can see the light</i>

16:02.480 --> 16:07.725
<i>♪ Pack my bags
and let's get moving</i>

16:10.080 --> 16:15.564
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm bound
to drift awhile</i>

16:17.680 --> 16:20.365
<i>♪ Though I'm gone</i>

16:20.520 --> 16:24.127
<i>♪ You don't have to worry</i>

16:25.560 --> 16:30.487
<i>♪ Long as I can see the light</i>

16:32.880 --> 16:37.647
<i>♪ Long as I can see the light</i>

16:44.920 --> 16:49.084
<i>♪ Guess I've got that old
traveling bone</i>

16:52.480 --> 16:56.804
<i>♪ 'Cause this feeling
won't leave me alone</i>

17:00.240 --> 17:02.686
<i>♪ But I won't</i>

17:02.840 --> 17:06.970
<i>♪ Won't be losing my way, no</i>

17:08.000 --> 17:10.162
<i>♪ Long as I can see the light ♪</i>

17:10.319 --> 17:13.449
on... Mm.

17:17.839 --> 17:22.128
Mm-mm. Mm-mm.
Give me some love. That's right.

17:22.359 --> 17:23.964
<i>Uh...</i>

17:28.440 --> 17:29.601
<i>Uh...</i>

17:31.040 --> 17:33.327
Elliott, Elliott, Elliott.

17:35.280 --> 17:36.327
<i>Uh.</i>

17:37.960 --> 17:40.486
Every time I come out here,

17:40.640 --> 17:44.008
I tell myself, "One day, Rowena,

17:44.160 --> 17:47.926
you're gonna get Elliott
to invite us all out for a swim."

17:48.080 --> 17:51.641
You got a plan for Eloise
in light of all this?

17:51.880 --> 17:54.406
Not sure, not yet.

17:54.560 --> 17:56.767
Probably just love her.
That's the plan for now.

17:56.920 --> 17:58.524
Mm.

17:58.720 --> 18:02.645
She's got a whole lot of family
down with me. Mm-hm.

18:02.800 --> 18:06.850
I got my Kristen, and her cute little
gay family across the street.

18:07.000 --> 18:09.810
And her darlin'
little music teacher wife.

18:09.960 --> 18:13.203
Got two of my brother's girls
and my sister's boy.

18:13.400 --> 18:17.530
- All on my dime.
- Go figure.

18:18.640 --> 18:22.690
Well, you can always come visit,
come for a swim. How's that?

18:24.040 --> 18:26.611
I know you don't like my boy.

18:26.760 --> 18:29.081
I know you're still angry,
but this isn't about Reggie.

18:29.240 --> 18:31.041
He's not in the picture.
This is about Eloise.

18:31.080 --> 18:32.844
OK, got it.

18:33.000 --> 18:35.765
Got it. Jeez...

18:35.920 --> 18:39.367
Have a sandwich, Rowena.
Maybe a drink. All right?

18:39.520 --> 18:40.646
Enjoy yourself.

18:40.800 --> 18:44.043
I'd go somewhere and play some poker
if I was looking to enjoy myself.

18:44.200 --> 18:45.725
Maybe a Lakers game.

18:45.880 --> 18:47.723
Not here for a good time.

18:47.880 --> 18:51.566
- It's a wake, remember?
- Fine.

18:52.560 --> 18:53.971
Point taken.

19:04.600 --> 19:07.046
Toothpaste, toothbrush,
in your mouth, now.

19:09.040 --> 19:10.724
- What?
- Madder.

19:10.920 --> 19:13.321
You gotta be madder at me
like you mean it.

19:16.840 --> 19:18.604
Let me, uh...

19:18.800 --> 19:20.564
Want me to just go out and start again?

19:20.760 --> 19:21.966
Yeah.

19:25.920 --> 19:28.082
Eloise, you brush those teeth!
I mean it.

19:28.240 --> 19:30.686
Don't make me come in there
and have to say it twice.

19:30.840 --> 19:32.330
Nice.

19:44.800 --> 19:47.326
Aren't you going
to drive me to school?

19:51.240 --> 19:52.321
Yes.

19:52.480 --> 19:54.050
<i>GK.</i>

20:13.480 --> 20:14.925
Morning.

20:28.000 --> 20:30.810
You're in the third grade
and you're dealing...

20:36.960 --> 20:40.442
You're in the third grade and you're
dealing with this level math?

20:40.600 --> 20:44.571
I didn't deal with
this stuff until... ever.

20:44.760 --> 20:47.161
Does that mean
you're not going to help me?

20:48.720 --> 20:50.006
Of course not.

20:52.000 --> 20:53.525
Not at all. Let's take a...

20:54.520 --> 20:56.329
Let's take a shot at this.

20:56.520 --> 20:59.364
I'm not very good at math, though,
all right? I'm a lawyer.

21:00.560 --> 21:03.006
- You know what we're good at, right?
- What?

21:04.200 --> 21:05.361
Nothing.

21:06.360 --> 21:09.125
That was...

21:09.280 --> 21:10.611
That was a joke.

21:19.720 --> 21:24.044
Hi. I'm Duvan. Are you Elliott?

21:24.200 --> 21:26.521
Yes, yes. Uh...

21:26.720 --> 21:28.210
- Nice to meet you. Come on in.
- Thank you.

21:28.360 --> 21:29.486
Come on in.

21:30.760 --> 21:32.808
My résumé.

21:39.400 --> 21:41.209
A list of my study courses.

21:51.880 --> 21:54.281
A paper that I wrote
for the National Math Board

21:54.440 --> 21:57.410
on systemic dysfunction
in proper Algebraic education.

22:00.960 --> 22:03.281
That's good. This is good.

22:05.160 --> 22:07.845
- You want a drink?
- I would... like a drink, yes.

22:08.000 --> 22:11.368
OK, good.
What do you like? I got the works.

22:11.520 --> 22:14.524
Oh, no, just a water, please.

22:17.600 --> 22:21.730
And... another paper that I wrote.

22:21.880 --> 22:23.644
In the flyer, my piano lessons.

22:23.800 --> 22:27.521
I have a fall special that I'm currently
running that offers the piano lessons

22:27.680 --> 22:30.206
half off when purchased with tutoring
in either math, science

22:30.360 --> 22:32.966
or any of the eight languages
that I have listed there.

22:33.160 --> 22:35.527
You sure you don't want a cocktail?

22:35.680 --> 22:37.842
You're very, very qualified, Duvan.
That's good.

22:38.040 --> 22:40.611
Because Eloise, she's special.

22:40.760 --> 22:45.800
She lost her grandmother... my wife,
about three weeks ago in a car crash.

22:45.960 --> 22:48.201
I don't want her to fall behind
in her studies.

22:48.360 --> 22:50.362
- What about her mother?
- My daughter?

22:50.520 --> 22:54.969
She died during childbirth.
She had congenital heart problems.

22:57.040 --> 22:59.600
My wife and I weren't with her
at the hospital when she was born.

22:59.640 --> 23:02.450
Weren't invited. Or included.

23:05.440 --> 23:09.331
We, uh... We weren't called,
let's just put it that way.

23:11.480 --> 23:14.768
The doctors weren't aware
of her medical history.

23:16.480 --> 23:20.326
I lost my father, my grandfather
and two of my brothers.

23:20.480 --> 23:24.963
Killed by murderers,
along with 300 others from my village.

23:27.480 --> 23:28.641
I'm sorry.

23:28.840 --> 23:31.844
A paper I wrote on literature's
effect on grief

23:32.000 --> 23:36.130
for the library of the National
Endowment for Children's Literature.

23:36.280 --> 23:40.683
I have also written a paper
on channeling our emotions

23:40.840 --> 23:45.448
in a positive direction using meditation
and alternative grief counseling.

23:45.600 --> 23:47.807
That's good, but there's gonna
be something else, all right?

23:47.960 --> 23:50.167
It's not gonna be just Eloise.

23:50.360 --> 23:51.771
It's gonna be me as well.

23:51.920 --> 23:56.403
I'm gonna need a little tutoring
in math myself.

23:56.560 --> 23:58.562
Is that gonna be a problem?

23:58.720 --> 24:01.610
No, that will not be a problem at all.

24:01.760 --> 24:05.207
I do, however, charge by the student.

24:05.360 --> 24:08.045
Yeah, I'm sure you do.

24:08.200 --> 24:09.440
<i>Elliott, it's Rowena.</i>

24:09.600 --> 24:11.568
Now I need you to pick up that phone
and call me, baby.

24:11.760 --> 24:14.240
I know you're in pain.
Your pain is my pain.

24:14.400 --> 24:16.209
That little girl is my little girl. OK?

